name: DNA topoisomerase
classes: Sole sub-subclass for isomerases that do not belong in the other subclasses
reaction: ATP-independent breakage of single-stranded DNA, followed by passage and rejoining
comment: These enzymes bring about the conversion of one topological isomer of DNA into another, e.g., the relaxation of superhelical turns in DNA, the interconversion of simple and knotted rings of single-stranded DNA, and the intertwisting of single-stranded rings of complementary sequences, cf. EC 5.99.1.3 DNA topoisomerase (ATP-hydrolysing).
